[To] Beniua Busuka

[NPC Internal] Hello Beniua, anything going on lately?
[NPC] Beniua: Hail Darvingar.
[NPC] Beniua: A lot, as always.
[NPC] Beniua: Too few supplies, too few fighters, too many troubles.

[NPC Narrate] Beniua Busuka smiles.

[NPC] Beniua: There's always something keeping me busy but nothing I should bother others about, it is my job after all...

[NPC Narrate] Beniua Busuka pauses, but then concedes.

[NPC] Beniua: However, recently I have encountered something that worries me, a lot, it might interest an adventurer like you.
[NPC] Beniua: I guess you've already seen a riverling, but did you hear about them having found, well, a king?

[NPC Internal] A riverling king?

[NPC Narrate] Beniua Busuka starts to smile but it seems out of nervousness.

[NPC] Beniua: Yes, king seems like as good a term as any to describe him...
[NPC] Beniua: It seems one of the riverlings near the fortress became just that!
[NPC] Beniua: I'm troubled how this might become a problem as their tribe is so close off the road to the fortress.
[NPC] Beniua: Too close.
[NPC] Beniua: We could use someone to investigate this further.
[NPC] Beniua: Might you?

[NPC Internal] Sure thing. Is there anything else I should know before going?

[NPC] Beniua: As far as I'm aware, it would be wiser not to go and investigate this matter alone.
[NPC] Beniua: Being united by this king will likely make them stronger and even more of a fearless foe...

[NPC Internal] Alright, thank you Beniua.

[NPC] Beniua: One last thing, Darvingar.
[NPC] Beniua: I take my job very seriously and when a matter arises I ensure to solve it fully.
[NPC] Beniua: I think it would be best to bring this to the attention of a specialist.
[NPC] Beniua: Once you have observed the king and his behaviour, and if you are interested, you should contact Durok Rrecrok.
[NPC] Beniua: The kran or kras colleagues are more competent then any of us to then deal with this problem in the best way possible.
[NPC] Beniua: And to be honest if they do not take this in charge, we will have to settle this forcibly.

[NPC Internal] I think it's always better to refer to a specialist. I will try to observe it before talking to Durok.

[NPC Narrate] Beniua Busuka nods.

[NPC] Beniua: Thank you, Darvingar.
[NPC] Beniua: I will report this in my logs.
[NPC] Beniua: Please tell Durok or whoever will take this in charge, to contact me.

[Info] you need to see Zoltak before proceeding. You'll find him in the lake near the fortress ramp

[To] Durok Rrecrok

