[NPC] Durok: Hello YOU!
[NPC] Durok: Well hummmmm I am glad Beniua and yourself chose to inform the science association about this!
[NPC] Durok: To be honest, I have already heard about this.
[NPC] Durok: First because a fisherman reported it to me, bless errrrrrr him.
[NPC] Durok: And second, hummmmmm, because it is not the errrr first time this has happened.

[NPC Internal] Really?

[NPC] Durok: I have errr discussed with a friend of mine who is more versed into the animal studies.
[NPC] Durok: As you may know, my hummmm specialty is rather the insects but ermmmm..anyway.
[NPC] Durok: Kra said that occasionally, a riverling will grow errrr stronger than the others and then be able to ascend to the "throne" by challenging his potential rivals.
[NPC] Durok: Once established, it will hummmmmmm "organise" its tribe in a more structured way and therefore errrrrrr be a real threat for anything or anyone in the area.

[NPC Internal] Oh. But why does it grow bigger? Does he have other particularities?

[NPC] Durok: Hummmmm Kra does not exactly know why but sometimes, one specimen will grow taller.
[NPC] Durok: Their skull expands in width making their eyes more hummmm separated, allowing them to see in a wider angle.
[NPC] Durok: This also develops their sense for smelling and noticing foes.
[NPC] Durok: All of this and their significantly longer teeth, give them a errrrrrrmm certain advantage on their tribe mates.
[NPC] Durok: Though, being water creature, they still are sensitive to fire and in extent to Red Way magic.

[NPC Internal] Do you consider the riverling tribe a threat then, now that they have a king?

[NPC] Durok: I ermmm suppose you mean a threat to the residents of the fortress and or the caravans?
[NPC] Durok: Obviously, I would say yes.
[NPC] Durok: On the other hand, if a hummmmmmmm invasion occurs, they will ferociously defend their territory against the invading...mmmmmmm...beasts, technically becoming an ally to our soldiers.
[NPC] Durok: Beware though, that the riverlings will defend their king to death if necessary. 

